[SN]TITLE[SN]
Colchester United 2-0 Bradford City

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Colchester United claimed their fourth consecutive League One victory with a comfortable win over Bradford City.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Callum Harriott opened the scoring when his low, angled drive snuck under keeper Brad Jones' attempted parry.
Colchester grew in confidence before Marvin Sordell's calm finish, set up by Owen Garvan's reverse pass, extended their lead.
Tony McMahon came close for Bradford in the second half, but his strike from 20 yards out hit the underside of the bar.
